[cid:image016.jpg@01DB972D.5DC75A70]

I wanted to check in regarding your support ticket 00417457. We haven’t heard from you in a while, and I just wanted to see if you still need assistance with this issue.

If you’re still experiencing problems or have any updates to share, please let me know. If the issue has been resolved, I can go ahead and close the ticket on my end.

Ticket Number: 00417457
Ticket Subject: Client Install/Uninstall Issues
Ticket Details: Some members of our IT team are having difficulties installing and uninstalling the client. Some of them performed a manual uninstall when it was giving them issues and hence their computers appeared as offline in the console. When trying to manually re-install using the client software downloaded from the console, they received the port error in the screenshot attached. The client did seem to partially install as it was in their programs and features, but when attempting to uninstall that it gave the MSI error in the other screenshot attached. In my case, I uninstalled from the console since I was showing as online, and was able to manually install the downloaded client without any issue. Our server version is 5.9.4.0, but that is not available from your ticket question drop down yet so I selected another.

Thank you!
